Kidnapped Son of Kaspersky Lab’s Founder Freed Outside Moscow

-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 
2011-04-24T12:48:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-24/kidnapped-son-of-kaspersky-lab-s-founder-freed-outside-moscow.html
Russian security forces freed the
son of Russian software businessman Evgeny Kaspersky held
hostage for a 3 million-euro ($4.4 million) ransom outside
Moscow.  Ivan Kaspersky, 20, was freed unharmed today and at least
four people were arrested in connection with the April 19
kidnapping, Moscow police spokesman Viktor Biryukov told state
television Rossiya-24. No ransom was paid, RIA Novosti reported
today, citing unidentified security officers.  Evgeny Kaspersky, the founder of Kaspersky Lab, an anti-
virus computer security company, is  Russia ’s 125th richest man
with an estimated fortune of $800 million, according to Forbes
magazine.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
 dmaternovsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  